Introduced Version
HOUSE BILL No. 1329
_____
DIGEST OF INTRODUCED BILL
Citations Affected: IC 2-5-50.1.
Synopsis: Real property assessment. Establishes the real property
assessment task force (task force) to review issues related to real
property assessment in Indiana. Sets forth membership, and requires
the task force to issue a report to the general assembly not later than
November 1, 2026.
Effective: Upon passage.
Clere, Thompson, O'Brien,
DeLaney
January 6, 2026, read first time and referred to Committee on Ways and Means.
2026 IN 1329—LS 7022/DI 120

Introduced
Second Regular Session of the 124th General Assembly (2026)
PRINTING CODE. Amendments: Whenever an existing statute (or a section of the Indiana
Constitution) is being amended, the text of the existing provision will appear in this style type,
additions will appear in this style type, and deletions will appear in this style type.
Additions: Whenever a new statutory provision is being enacted (or a new constitutional
provision adopted), the text of the new provision will appear in this style type. Also, the
word NEW will appear in that style type in the introductory clause of each SECTION that adds
a new provision to the Indiana Code or the Indiana Constitution.
Conflict reconciliation: Text in a statute in this style type or this style type reconciles conflicts
between statutes enacted by the 2025 Regular Session of the General Assembly.
HOUSE BILL No. 1329
A BILL FOR AN ACT to amend the Indiana Code concerning
taxation.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
1 SECTION 1. IC 2-5-50.1 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE
2 AS A NEW CHAPTER TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
3 UPON PASSAGE]:
4 Chapter 50.1. Real Property Assessment Task Force
5 Sec. 1. As used in this chapter, "task force" refers to the real
6 property assessment task force established by section 2 of this
7 chapter.
8 Sec. 2. The real property assessment task force is established.
9 Sec. 3. (a) The task force consists of the following members:
10 (1) Two (2) legislative members appointed by the speaker.
11 (2) Two (2) legislative members appointed by the minority
12 leader of the house.
13 (3) Two (2) legislative members appointed by the president
14 pro tempore.
15 (4) Two (2) legislative members appointed by the minority
16 leader of the senate.
17 (5) The following members appointed jointly by the speaker
2026 IN 1329—LS 7022/DI 120

2
1 and the president pro tempore upon the recommendation of
2 each represented organization:
3 (A) An individual representing the Indiana Association of
4 Realtors.
5 (B) An individual representing the Association of Indiana
6 Counties.
7 (C) An individual representing the Indiana County
8 Assessors Association.
9 (D) An individual representing Accelerate Indiana
10 Municipalities.
11 (E) An individual representing the Hoosier State Chapter
12 of the Appraisal Institute.
13 (F) An individual representing the Indiana Builders
14 Association.
15 (G) An individual representing the Indiana Bankers
16 Association.
17 (H) An individual representing the Indiana Apartment
18 Association.
19 (I) An individual representing the Indiana Manufactured
20 Housing Association.
21 (b) The speaker shall designate a member appointed under
22 subsection (a)(1) or (a)(2) as a co-chair of the task force.
23 (c) The president pro tempore shall designate a member
24 appointed under subsection (a)(3) or (a)(4) as a co-chair of the task
25 force.
26 (d) A vacancy on the task force must be filled by the
27 appointment of a replacement member by the appointing authority
28 identified in subsection (a).
29 Sec. 4. (a) A majority of the members of the task force
30 constitutes a quorum.
31 (b) The affirmative vote of a majority of the members at a
32 meeting at which a quorum is present is necessary for the task
33 force to take official action, other than to meet and take testimony.
34 (c) The task force shall meet at the call of the co-chairs.
35 Sec. 5. All meetings of the task force shall be open to the public
36 in accordance with and subject to IC 5-14-1.5. All records of the
37 task force shall be subject to the requirements of IC 5-14-3.
38 Sec. 6. The task force shall do the following:
39 (1) Review other state approaches to real property
40 assessment, including the use in other states of automated
41 valuation model (AVM) systems for real property assessment.
42 (2) Study and make recommendations regarding how
2026 IN 1329—LS 7022/DI 120

3
1 automated valuation model (AVM) systems should be
2 incorporated into real property assessment in Indiana.
3 (3) Study the extent to which existing assessment methods and
4 procedures have led to inaccurate and nonuniform real
5 property assessments within classes of properties and across
6 classes of properties.
7 (4) Study the extent to which ratio studies are effective in
8 measuring the accuracy and equity of assessments.
9 (5) Study and consider the implications if Indiana were to
10 move from its current market value in use assessment
11 standard to a fair market value assessment standard.
12 (6) Study and make recommendations regarding whether
13 township assessors should be eliminated.
14 (7) Study and make recommendations regarding whether the
15 office of county assessor should be eliminated and its
16 functions and duties transferred to the county auditor.
17 Sec. 7. The task force shall, not later than November 1, 2026,
18 report the task force's findings and recommendations in an
19 electronic format under IC 5-14-6 to the executive director of the
20 legislative services agency for distribution to the members of the
21 general assembly.
22 Sec. 8. The legislative services agency shall staff the task force.
23 Sec. 9. Each legislative member and each lay member of the task
24 force is entitled to receive the same per diem, mileage, and travel
25 allowances paid to individuals serving as legislative and lay
26 members, respectively, on an interim study committee established
27 by the legislative council.
28 Sec. 10. The task force's expenses, including the payment of per
29 diem, mileage, and travel allowances under section 9 of this
30 chapter, are payable from amounts appropriated to the legislative
31 council.
32 Sec. 11. This chapter expires January 1, 2027.
33 SECTION 2. An emergency is declared for this act.
